  "instructions": [
    "Preheat broiler to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Whisk coconut milk, coriander powder, cumin powder, turmeric powder, red pepper flakes, and salt in a bowl.",
    "Add the marinade to the chicken and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Thread the marinated chicken onto skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.",
    "Place the skewers on a broiler pan and brush with coconut oil.",
    "Broil the chicken for 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally, until cooked through.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, prepare the peanut sauce by blending peanuts, onion, garlic, and lemon juice in a food processor.",
    "Season the peanut sauce with salt and set aside.",
    "Serve the chicken satay with peanut sauce for dipping.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve immediately."
  ],
